
[1]ignominy

   IG'NOMINY, n. [L. ignominia; in and nomen, against name or reputation.]
   Public disgrace; shame; reproach; dishonor; infamy.

   Their generals have been received with honor after their defeat; yours
   with ignominy after conquest.

   Vice begins in mistake, and ends in ignominy.
